  "title": "Актуализировать публичный API-профиль Electron2D по принятому Godot-scope контуру",
  "description": "## T-1137 [x] P0: Актуализировать публичный API-профиль Electron2D по принятому Godot-scope контуру\n\n- Создана: 2026-07-09T18:08:00+03:00\n- Завершена: 2026-07-10T23:54:01+03:00\n- Принята внешним аудитом: primary r32 `VERDICT: ACCEPT`; corrective control r40 `VERDICT: ACCEPT`; independent clean-control r43 `VERDICT: ACCEPT`.\n- Архивная причина: пользователь поручил выполнить полный goal workflow T-1137, включая архивирование после сохранённого финального clean-control `ACCEPT`; все actionable findings закрыты или переданы в отдельные zero-context follow-up задачи.\n- Коммит: fix(api): synchronize Electron2D public API profile\n- Состояние: accepted/closed\n- Приоритет: P0\n- Execution class: `completed`\n- Scheduling tier: `accepted`\n- Зависимости: T-0241, T-0242\n- Ссылки:\n  - Профиль API: `data/api/electron2d-public-api-profile.json`\n  - Сгенерированный манифест: `data/api/electron2d-api-manifest.json`\n  - Генератор/верификаторы: `eng/Electron2D.ApiManifestGenerator/`; `eng/Electron2D.Build/`\n  - Публичная документация API: `docs/documentation/api-manifest.md`; `docs/release-management/api-compatibility.md`; `data/documentation/`\n  - Исходный код и тесты: `src/Electron2D/`; `src/Electron2D.Editor/`; `tests/`\n  - Финальный gate-потребитель: `T-0980`\n\n### Execution contract\n\n- Task type: profile/generated synchronization with minimal runtime/tooling alignment.\n- Ready-to-start:\n  - task state is `open`;\n  - dependencies `T-0241` and `T-0242` are accepted/closed or have saved `ACCEPT`;\n  - current user explicitly asked to create this task for the already prepared diff and to run audit-loop for that diff.\n- Stop conditions:\n  - work attempts to mark every ROADMAP §2 class task accepted/closed;\n  - work changes unsupported/deferred decisions without an explicit owner decision;\n  - work expands into class-done runtime implementation beyond the profile/generated/root-object alignment already present in the diff;\n  - audit scope tries to use `T-0980` as the changed-task id instead of this task.\n- May change:\n  - files named in this task's links that are already part of the current cross-cutting diff;\n  - task notes, diary and generated audit artifacts for this task;\n  - regenerated API/docs artifacts only through repository generators/verifiers.\n- Must not change:\n  - unrelated ROADMAP §2 class task acceptance boxes;\n  - unrelated runtime/editor behavior not required by current profile/generated synchronization;\n  - release gates, saved verdict reports or completed-task archives without the audit-loop evidence required by the workflow.\n- Required outputs:\n  - synchronized `data/api/electron2d-public-api-profile.json`;\n  - synchronized generated manifest/docs indexes;\n  - evidence that public Godot `Object` maps to `ElectronObject` while ordinary CLR `object` remains unchanged;\n  - evidence that `RenderingServer` is approved and exported as the public 2D rendering server boundary while RD/3D/spatial/VisualShader backend surfaces remain outside exported public API;\n  - saved primary audit verdict for this task; control audit only if required by the current goal and workflow.\n- Required commands:\n  - `dotnet build src/Electron2D/Electron2D.csproj --no-restore -v:minimal`\n  - `dotnet build src/Electron2D.Editor/Electron2D.Editor.csproj --no-restore -v:minimal`\n  - `dotnet build eng/Electron2D.Build/Electron2D.Build.csproj --no-restore -v:minimal`\n  - `dotnet build eng/Electron2D.ApiManifestGenerator/Electron2D.ApiManifestGenerator.csproj --no-restore -v:minimal`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- update api-manifest --check`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- update wiki --check --output .github/wiki`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- update docs --check`\n  - focused unit/integration tests for touched public API/generated-surface paths\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify api-compatibility --wiki-path .github/wiki`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify ui-public-api-gate --wiki-path .github/wiki`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify public-api-documentation --wiki-path .github/wiki`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify docs`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify licenses`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify audit-contracts`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify audit-followups`\n  - `git diff --check`\n- External audit:\n  - required for the current goal;\n  - package id must be `T-1137`;\n  - package scope must state that this task records profile/generated synchronization and does not close all ROADMAP §2 class tasks.\n\n### Самодостаточное описание\n\nЗадача фиксирует уже подготовленный cross-cutting diff после серии решений владельца проекта о будущем публичном API Electron2D: какие Godot 4.x классы и built-in типы входят в 2D/C#/editor/tools/networking/audio/text profile, какие остаются `Deferred`, какие явно запрещены как 3D/XR/RD/VisualShader/GDScript/GDExtension или иначе не входят в public API.\n\nЭто не `T-0980` и не финальное закрытие ROADMAP §2. Все class tasks остаются отдельными задачами готовности реализации. Эта задача отвечает только за согласованность текущего профиля, generated manifest/docs, минимальных runtime/tooling rename/visibility adjustments and verification evidence для уже внесённого diff.\n\n### Критерии приёмки\n\n- [x] `data/api/electron2d-public-api-profile.json` содержит текущие approved/deferred/unsupported decisions по обсуждённому Godot-scope контуру без известных несинхронизированных generated artifacts.\n- [x] `data/api/electron2d-api-manifest.json`, локальные docs indexes and API docs regenerated and pass `--check` commands.\n- [x] Public root mapping зафиксирован как `ElectronObject` for Godot `Object`; `Electron2D.Object` unsupported; plain CLR `object`, `System.Object` and `Variant.Type.Object` are not mechanically renamed.\n- [x] `RenderingServer` is exported as approved public API with a 2D/HLSL/RD-free contract; forbidden RD/3D/spatial/VisualShader/backend surfaces are not exported by public API gates.\n- [x] Relevant builds, tests, docs, license, public API and audit follow-up checks pass in the current session.\n- [x] External audit package for `T-1137` receives saved `VERDICT: ACCEPT`; control audit is skipped only if the current goal's \"first ACCEPT needs no control\" rule applies.\n- [x] Task notes and diary record exact checks, package paths and verdict paths.\n\n### Подзадачи\n\n- [x] Проверить ready-to-start gate for `T-1137`.\n- [x] Rebuild or verify generated API/docs artifacts.\n- [x] Run local preflight checks and store package evidence.\n- [x] Create and verify `T-1137` audit package.\n- [x] Submit primary audit and process saved verdict.\n- [x] Update task notes and diary after verdict.\n\n### Заметки агента\n\n2026-07-09T18:08:00+03:00 - Создано по прямому решению владельца проекта как owning task для текущего cross-cutting diff. Эта задача не закрывает `T-0980` and does not mark ROADMAP §2 class tasks accepted; она даёт корректный `taskId` for audit package metadata and saved verdict path.\n\n2026-07-09T18:11:00+03:00 - Ready-to-start gate принят для audit-loop: `T-0241` and `T-0242` already accepted/closed, владелец явно создал `T-1137` for current diff, audit scope must use `T-1137` and must not close all ROADMAP §2 class tasks.\n\n2026-07-09T18:15:00+03:00 - Local preflight for `T-1137` r01 passed 16/16 checks with evidence under `.temp/audit-evidence/T-1137-r01/preflight`: runtime/build-tool/API-manifest-generator builds, generated API/wiki/docs `--check`, unit tests, focused `ApiManifestTests`, public API/doc verifiers, docs/licenses/audit-contracts/audit-followups and `git diff --check`.\n\n2026-07-09T18:20:00+03:00 - `audit package` r01 created and verified `.temp/audit/T-1137/T-1137-audit-r01.zip` with sidecar `.temp/audit/T-1137/T-1137-audit-r01.operator-workflow.zip`; operator workflow summary: `audit-package-message` exitCode `0`, `audit-package-verify` exitCode `0`.\n\n2026-07-09T18:47:00+03:00 - Superseding owner decision during r01 blocker closure: `RenderingServer` is public API. `T-1137` now treats `RenderingServer` as an approved/exported 2D rendering server boundary; `T-0736` remains the full class-done gate for complete Godot 4.7 parity, and RD/3D/spatial/VisualShader/concrete backend APIs remain forbidden.\n\n2026-07-09T18:58:00+03:00 - Saved primary audit report `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-1137-audit-r01.md` returned `VERDICT: NEEDS_FIXES` with blockers `B1` status semantics (`approved` was mislabeled as `parity_verified`), `B2` mechanical deferred-test rename of plain CLR `object`, and `B3` missing editor-build evidence after the then-assumed internal `RenderingServer`. Closure plan for r02: `profile.parity` now uses `profile_approved`; `DeferredCallTests` expects literal `object`; `RenderingServer` owner decision supersedes the old internal assumption and requires exported public 2D boundary evidence plus editor build, while full Godot parity remains in `T-0736`.\n\n2026-07-09T19:01:00+03:00 - Local preflight for `T-1137` r02 passed 20/20 checks with evidence under `.temp/audit-evidence/T-1137-r02/preflight` and sanitized evidence under `.temp/audit-evidence/T-1137-r02/preflight-sanitized`: runtime/editor/build-tool/API-manifest-generator builds, generated API/wiki/docs `--check`, `RenderingServerPublicApiTests`, `DeferredCallTests`, `ApiManifestTests`, CLI api-compare profile tests, `RenderingServerBackendTests`, public API/doc verifiers, docs/licenses/audit-contracts/audit-followups and `git diff --check`.\n\n2026-07-09T19:08:00+03:00 - Re-ran final `T-1137` r02 preflight after removing machine-local Android SDK/JDK fallback literals from `src/Electron2D.Cli/CliGeneralCommands.cs` and synchronizing `docs/export/android-arm64-export.md`; generated docs index was updated. Final r02 preflight passed the same 20/20 checks with sanitized evidence and no local absolute paths in evidence.\n\n2026-07-09T19:39:00+03:00 - Final `T-1137` r02 package route passed after adding a narrow audit-package regression for removed baseline Windows drive paths: final preflight passed 21/21 checks including `AuditPackageAllowsRemovedWindowsDrivePathsWhenRepoAfterIsClean`, sanitized evidence was rebuilt, and `audit package` created/verified `.temp/audit/T-1137/T-1137-audit-r02.zip` plus `.temp/audit/T-1137/T-1137-audit-r02.operator-workflow.zip`; operator workflow summary: `audit-package-message` exitCode `0`, `audit-package-verify` exitCode `0`.\n\n2026-07-09T19:41:00+03:00 - Blocked on external primary audit submission, not on package content: `audit submit --reuse-conversation` and `audit submit --new-conversation` for `.temp/audit/T-1137/T-1137-audit-r02.zip` both failed with `E2D-BUILD-AUDIT-SUBMIT-CODEX-CHROME-PROTOCOL` / `Debugger unattached` before creating `.temp/audit/T-1137/conversation-url-r02.txt`; `--download-report-only` against the existing r01 conversation did not produce a Markdown export. Saved r02 verdict file does not exist yet, so task cannot be accepted or committed.\n\n2026-07-09T19:42:00+03:00 - Goal continuation blocker report: READY-TO-START gate was checked again and did not pass because task state remains `blocked`, there is still no saved `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-1137-audit-r02.md`, no `.temp/audit/T-1137/conversation-url-r02.txt`, and no explicit current owner override to bypass the external submit blocker. Per `.codex/prompts/goal-task-workflow.md`, no production work, audit packaging, audit submit or commit was performed in this continuation.\n\n2026-07-09T19:44:00+03:00 - Goal continuation blocker report repeated: READY-TO-START gate still fails for the same external submit blocker. `T-1137` remains `blocked`, `.temp/audit/T-1137/T-1137-audit-r02.zip` exists, but there is no saved `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-1137-audit-r02.md`, no `.temp/audit/T-1137/conversation-url-r02.txt`, and no explicit current owner override. Per `.codex/prompts/goal-task-workflow.md`, no production work, audit packaging, audit submit or commit was performed in this continuation.\n\n2026-07-09T21:08:00+03:00 - Owner override received for the external submit blocker: user explicitly confirmed \"Продолжи аудит, все хорошо с браузером\". `T-1137` returned to `in progress`; next step is to rebuild the r02 audit package after the latest task/diary notes and retry official `audit submit` with `--browser-backend codex-chrome`.\n\n2026-07-09T21:22:00+03:00 - Saved primary audit report `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-1137-audit-r02.md` returned `VERDICT: NEEDS_FIXES`. Blocker synthesis for r03: `B1` is a task-scope hygiene failure, caused by an unrelated state mutation in `T-0092`; closure is to restore `T-0092` baseline `blocked` state and verify the next package diff no longer mutates that section. `B2` is the same parity-semantics failure class as r01 `B1`: profile approval was split from `profile.parity`, but generated manifest/CLI/docs/tests still emitted stale strict/full parity claims through zero `strictParitySummary`, `data.strictParity`, and message `API parity verified.`; closure must replace those with explicit `not_verified` parity evidence and add tests that reject the old full-parity signal without actual Godot 4.7 comparison evidence.\n\n2026-07-09T21:48:00+03:00 - Local preflight for `T-1137` r03 passed 22/22 checks with sanitized evidence under `.temp/audit-evidence/T-1137-r03/preflight-sanitized`: runtime/editor/build-tool/API-manifest-generator builds, generated API/wiki/docs `--check`, focused public API/deferred-call/API-manifest/CLI/rendering-server/audit-package tests, API/UI/docs/license/audit verifiers, `git diff --check`, `no-stale-strict-parity-claims`, and `t0092-state-baseline-check`. r03 closure: `T-0092` is restored to baseline `blocked`; generated manifest exposes `strictParityEvidence.status = not_verified`; CLI exposes `data.parityEvidence` and message \"API type is approved by the Electron2D public API profile.\"; docs/tests no longer claim strict/full parity without separate Godot `4.7-stable` evidence.\n\n2026-07-09T21:55:00+03:00 - Package-valid r03 closure update: saved `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-1137-audit-r02.md` contains a redacted reviewer phrase with redacted token/password placeholders in previous-verdict prose. The package scanner now allows that exact historical line only through the existing previous-verdict reviewer placeholder allowlist, with regression `AuditPackageAllowsKnownReviewerPlaceholderPhraseInPreviousVerdicts`. Additional checks passed: targeted test 1/1, `dotnet build eng/Electron2D.Build/Electron2D.Build.csproj --no-restore -v:minimal`, `verify audit-contracts`, `verify licenses`, and `git diff --check`.\n2026-07-09T22:32:00+03:00 - Saved primary audit report `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-1137-audit-r03.md` returned `VERDICT: NEEDS_FIXES` with blockers `B1`-`B4`. r04 closure implemented so far: `B1` restores ordinary CLR `object` in internal `Tween`/`AnimationPlayer` nested property-path helpers while keeping public `ElectronObject` targets and fixes `Variant.Equals(object?)` XML wording; `B2` removes stale strict-parity wording around `e2d api compare-godot` and adds a verifier guard for profile-approval/`not_verified` docs; `B3` updates API manifest docs from the historical empty-profile state to the current filled-profile gate and adds a verifier guard; `B4` restores `RenderingServer` and its nested enums in `CleanRuntimeBaselineTests`. Local closure checks passed so far: previously failing `TweenTests.PausePlayStopAndCustomStepUseDeterministicElapsedTime` now passes together with new nested CLR-object `Tween` and `AnimationPlayer` tests, `CleanRuntimeBaselineTests.RuntimeAssemblyExportsOnlyCurrentPublicBaselineTypes` passes, two new `RepositoryBuildToolTests` verifier regressions pass, and generated API manifest/docs index were refreshed.\n\n2026-07-09T22:55:00+03:00 - Owner decision during r04 closure: `T-0963` is no longer an active task because the Electron2D public API contour is already defined in `data/api/electron2d-public-api-profile.json`. The `T-0963` block was removed from active `TASKS.md` and moved to `data/completed-tasks/2026/07 Июль.md` as `superseded / невыполнена`; live docs/code now refer to manual profile `Deferred`/`Unsupported` rows instead of a separate task.\n\n2026-07-09T23:04:00+03:00 - r04 package route update: `audit package` created and verified `.temp/audit/T-1137/T-1137-audit-r04.zip` plus `.temp/audit/T-1137/T-1137-audit-r04.operator-workflow.zip` with package checks `8/8` and sidecar `audit-package-message`/`audit-package-verify` exitCode `0`. After that, owner requested a repository workflow rule against creating tests for every small change; `docs/repository/agent-workflow.md` now requires checking lifecycle value before adding a new test. `update docs --check`, `verify audit-contracts` and `git diff --check` passed for that rule. Because this changed a tracked workflow document after the first r04 ZIP, r04 must be rebuilt before external submit.\n\n2026-07-09T23:27:08+03:00 - Goal continuation blocker report: ready-to-start gate не пройден, потому что текущее поле задачи остаётся `Состояние: blocked`. Сохранённый r04 report уже существует и имеет `VERDICT: NEEDS_FIXES`; browser override от 21:08 закрыл прежний submit blocker и позволил получить r02-r04, но не даёт агенту права молча менять последующее состояние задачи. По `.codex/prompts/goal-task-workflow.md` в этой continuation не выполнялись production work, новые tests, audit packaging, audit submit или commit. Для продолжения r04 closure/r05 нужен явный текущий owner override с возвратом `T-1137` в `open` либо другой явно разрешённый ready-state.\n\n2026-07-09T23:28:15+03:00 - Goal continuation blocker report repeated: `T-1137` всё ещё имеет `Состояние: blocked`, r04 по-прежнему сохранён как `VERDICT: NEEDS_FIXES`, а нового owner override для возврата задачи в ready-state нет. Это второе последовательное повторение текущего task-state blocker после записи 23:27. По ready-to-start contract работа снова остановлена без production changes, tests, audit packaging, audit submit или commit.\n\n2026-07-09T23:29:03+03:00 - Current owner override received: пользователь явно распорядился «разблокировать T-1137 и продолжить аудит r05». `T-1137` переведена в `in progress`; task-state blocker снят, зависимости `T-0241`/`T-0242` остаются принятыми, дальнейшая работа ограничена r04 closure и официальным r05 audit loop.\n\n2026-07-09T23:31:32+03:00 - Saved report `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-1137-audit-r04.md` classified for r05. `B1` is a repeated parity-semantics documentation failure class from r01 B1/r02 B2/r03 B2: concrete example `missing types = 0` in `docs/releases/0.1-preview.md` bypassed a delimiter-specific guard. Class-level closure synchronizes the release contract to `profile_approved`/`parityEvidence.status = not_verified`, scans every current `e2d api compare-godot` contract path including release notes, and rejects strict-zero counters case-insensitively with either `:` or `=` plus surrounding whitespace; the existing focused verifier test covers neighboring case/delimiter variants. `B2` is a new ROADMAP canonical-line integrity class: deleting adjacent `T-0963` left `- - `T-0964``; closure restores exactly one canonical ``- `T-0964` - ...`` row and uses direct canonical-count evidence instead of a one-off new test. `F1` is actionable but outside current implementation scope and is transferred to `T-1138`; `I1` is explicitly non-actionable.\n\n2026-07-09T23:43:53+03:00 - r05 local closure preflight passed 10/10 with sanitized evidence under `.temp/audit-evidence/T-1137-r05/preflight-sanitized`: existing focused parity-claim regression, docs synchronization, API/docs/license/audit/follow-up verifiers, c